This paper discusses platform virtualization and resource management in grid computing, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). It also mentions the use of peer-to-peer technology, which could potentially fall under Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the development of open source projects, which could fall under Software Engineering (cs.SE). The mention of isolating failures and malicious code could potentially fall under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of virtual resource management at CERN, which could potentially fall under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
